1- bootstraping.ipynb produces csv files containing bootstrapped gene ids

2- each bootstrapping_{class}.ipynb uses the csv files and .npy, which is the output of SFS.py, to sum the corresponding per-gene zerofold and fourfold SFS across genes, while rounding projected counts to preserve the total number of site

3- The result is fed to MultiDFE 

4- omega_na.R processes MultiDFE outputs and produces omega_na (fixprob) per bootstrap in {class}.txt files

5- omega_a & alpha.R uses fixprob and popfly info to calculate omega_a and alpha


